  "texts": [
    "Grading is a fundamental aspect of educational assessment that serves as a crucial means of providing feedback from students to educators.",
    "Despite its importance, traditional grading methods, which rely on manual processes, face several challenges that hinder their effectiveness and ability to scale.",
    "Grading is an essential yet labor-intensive task that is prone to subjectivity and repetition, which poses significant challenges to assessment practices 1.",
    "While traditional methods, such as rubric-based evaluation and norm-referenced grading, aim for objectivity, they often fall short due to subjective biases and inconsistencies.",
    "These methods frequently fail to provide personalized feedback at scale, which is a critical component in enhancing the instructional value of assessments [2] [3] [4]."
